subSubSection.paragraph:
The
rufipes
subgroup comprises seven species known from China :
Harpalus eous Tschitschérine
;
H. griseus (Panzer)
;
H. jureceki (Jedlička)
;
H. roninus Bates
;
H. ussuriensis Chaudoir
;
H. rufipes (DeGeer)
;
H. aenigma
(Tschitschérine,); and one species distributed in Japan :
H. pseudophonoides Schauberger. These
species are characterized by the elytra densely pubescent throughout and the apical spur of protibia not dentate at margins.
